Cooperation between the two Courts of Auditors
A number of meetings of representatives of both Courts took place in the run-up to the parallel audit.
The participants in these meetings became familiar with the organisation of the financial administration, the legislation on VAT and the system of VAT administration in each other country.
The subject of the test phase was agreed at the May 2006 meeting.
The results of the test phase were evaluated at the next joint meeting in August 2006.
This meeting established a timetable for the subsequent procedure and identified the following audit topics for the parallel examinations: 1.
Registration of taxable persons.
2.
International passenger transport by bus – legislation in the Czech Republic and Germany.
3. international exchange of information, in particular financial officials' approach to the processing of requests for information and the verification of selected problems mentioned in the requests for information, as well as spontaneous information between the Czech Republic and Germany.
4. tax returns.
5.
Summary notifications.
6.
Statistical information on deliveries and acquisitions between the Czech Republic and Germany.
7. VAT risk management.
At a meeting to coordinate the further audit of the Sao and the BRH in December 2006, both sides became familiar with the examination procedure in the Czech Republic and Germany and discussed the results of the parallel examinations already achieved.
