VAT risk management
Risk management in the Czech Republic
In the Czech Republic, several organisational units at different levels of financial management are involved in risk management in the field of VAT.
Within the Czech Ministry of Finance, the following organisational units are responsible for risk management and the fight against VAT fraud:
The VAT Methodology and Economic Administration Department or its Risk Management Unit will look into the identification of potential risk areas for tax revenues and evaluate trends in these risks in national and intra-Community trade.
At national level, this body coordinates the criterion of "credibility of VAT returns" and uses the MIAS data to detect possible tax evasion in intra-Community supplies and acquisitions.
Based on data on the Czech Republic's trade balance, it evaluates non-risk goods, prepares risk management in the field of VAT in a conceptual way and cooperates in this field with the relevant EC institutions and the other Member States.
The International Sales Tax Assistance Department shall, inter alia, provide for the exchange of information, contribute to the establishment and maintenance of a relevant information database, assess the data of other Member States available in the MIAS system, disclose to the public and is responsible for other forms of intergovernmental mutual assistance within the meaning of Council Regulation (EC) 1798 / 2003.
