Each time he registered, he did not apply for the allocation of a VAT number, but only a tax number which would apply to Germany.
Although it is not normally possible in Germany to assign a VAT number retroactively to a taxpayer, this was done retroactively by the German financial administration's competent expert in 2006 as of 1 May 2004.
The German CLO agrees a VAT ID number retroactively if the clear trader has not caused the delayed allocation, e.g. if the CLO caused the delay following the taxpayer's request to grant a VAT ID number.. "
In that case, the CLO grants the VAT number retroactively because the trader does not need a valid VAT number for intra-Community supplies under Paragraph 6 of the Ustst.
Conversely, a German acquirer does not need the (valid) VAT number of its supplier to explain the intra-Community acquisition.
Because of these differences in procedures between Member States, the German CLO granted the VAT number retroactively in this particular case.
